# Static archive of GameCon 2003 (reconstructed from the Internet Archive).
#
# The 2003 festival ran 10.-13. 7. 2003 in OLOMOUC (DDM, tř. 17. listopadu +
# nearby university dorms). It was run by the Altar publishing house, and in
# 2003 GameCon was a SECTION of the whole altar.cz publisher site (path
# altar.cz/gamecon/) — the same path-era as 2004/2005, older than the
# gamecon.altar.cz subdomain (2006-2008).
#
# Scope: the GameCon pages (~27 /gamecon/ pages, incl. the Mistrovství v DrD
# results archive vysledky95..vysledky03) served at the root, PLUS the Altar
# publisher-site nav menu it links to: the section landing pages (/altar/*,
# /arena/, /battletech/, /drd/, /dech/, /hexaedr/, /akce/, /prog/, /odkazy/,
# /kontakt/, /help/) and the game-relevant /cgi/doc/* document tree (DrD rules
# & FAQ, BattleTech, Aréna, Talisman, Pelennor). All restored from
# web.archive.org, transcoded WINDOWS-1250 -> UTF-8 (with an injected
# <meta charset>, since the source declared charset only via the HTTP header).
#
# Still out of scope (themed 404): dynamic CGI (/cgi/search.cgi, /cgi/doc/katalog),
# the product catalog, and links deeper than Wayback captured. The /cgi/doc tree
# was a catalog-backed app — ~100 intermediate index pages were only ever
# captured as runtime-error pages and were dropped, so a few sub-paths 404 (their
# leaf pages survive and are reachable directly). Assets (stylesheets/default.css,
# img/*) are served at their original absolute paths.

DirectoryIndex index.html
ErrorDocument 404 /404.html

# No directory listings: an orphaned dir (its index page was a dropped error
# capture) must fall to the themed 404, never expose a file listing.
Options -Indexes

<IfModule mod_rewrite.c>
    RewriteEngine On

    # Serve real files directly (pages at root, assets under their paths).
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -f
    RewriteRule ^ - [L]

    # Serve a real directory only if it actually has an index.html; otherwise
    # fall through to the themed 404 (no autoindex listing for orphaned dirs).
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -d
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME}/index.html -f
    RewriteRule ^ - [L]

    # Homepage.
    RewriteRule ^$  index.html [L]

    # Everything else (cross-site Altar chrome, uncaptured) -> themed 404.
    RewriteRule ^.*$ - [R=404,L]
</IfModule>
